HEADWORD: Dovecote
<hw>Dove"cote`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small house or box, raised to
a considerable height above the ground, and having compartments, in
which domestic pigeons breed; a dove house.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like an eagle in a <qex>dovecote</qex>, I⟦br⟧
Fluttered your Volscians in Corioli.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dove-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
